Elixir REPL is called Interactive Elixir and abbreviated as IEx.
%
Mix is a build tool that ships with Elixir that provides tasks for
creating, compiling, testing your application, managing its
dependencies and much more.
%
To invoke an erlang function from within elixir, use the following
syntax:

    {colon}{erlang_module_name}{dot}{function_name}(params)

For example,

iex(2)> :crypto.strong_rand_bytes(8)
<<55, 72, 194, 212, 29, 112, 56, 195>>

Here, `:crypto` is the erlang module name and `strong_rand_bytes` is
the function name.

The same function in erlang shell is as follows:

2> crypto:strong_rand_bytes(8).
<<82,108,14,42,155,76,49,52>>
%
The best thing to do is create a lagom number of processes.
Erlang comes from Sweden, and the word lagom loosely translated means

    "not too few, not too many, just about right."

Some say that this summarizes the Swedish character.

― Joe Armstrong, Programming Erlang: Software for a Concurrent World

Source: https://www.goodreads.com/work/quotes/794755-programming-erlang-software-for-a-concurrent-world
